197
00:10:11,903 --> 00:10:13,446
This is Grandmother Mago.

198
00:10:13,530 --> 00:10:15,990
The dark background
symbolizes the unknown world.

199
00:10:16,074 --> 00:10:17,408
- Okay.
- Stepping into the unknown.

200
00:10:17,492 --> 00:10:20,620
Now, if you look at her,
she's ready to run.

201
00:10:20,703 --> 00:10:22,914
She's holding her skirt, ready to run.

202
00:10:23,623 --> 00:10:25,667
If you ask me about overseas expansion,

203
00:10:25,750 --> 00:10:28,670
- I'd say making it happen…
- Yes.

204
00:10:28,753 --> 00:10:31,965
…will be the main part
of the second chapter in your life.

205
00:10:36,636 --> 00:10:38,847
Your reading is impressive.

206
00:10:38,930 --> 00:10:40,890
I'll trust the Grandmother Mago card,

207
00:10:40,974 --> 00:10:43,268
hike up my skirt like she has,

208
00:10:43,351 --> 00:10:45,186
and head to the US.

209
00:10:45,270 --> 00:10:48,565
If you feel stuck, shout up at the sky.

210
00:10:48,648 --> 00:10:50,150
- "I'll make it happen!"
- Good.

211
00:10:50,233 --> 00:10:51,693
"I'm Good Luck Esther!"

212
00:10:55,071 --> 00:10:57,448
- This is all very interesting.
- Yeah?

213
00:10:59,742 --> 00:11:00,743
She's having fun.

214
00:11:01,619 --> 00:11:04,455
- Can I ask a question?
- Of course, go ahead.

215
00:11:04,539 --> 00:11:06,958
My husband is 2 years younger than me.

216
00:11:07,041 --> 00:11:09,210
- Okay.
- Dr. Hong Hyegul.

217
00:11:09,294 --> 00:11:11,212
Let me have a look.

218
00:11:11,296 --> 00:11:12,714
She's reading her husband.

219
00:11:15,842 --> 00:11:17,844
This card says pretty much the same.

220
00:11:19,929 --> 00:11:21,389
Here's what it says.

221
00:11:21,472 --> 00:11:24,767
To be honest, your husband's income

222
00:11:24,851 --> 00:11:25,852
is like a drop in the ocean.

223
00:11:28,438 --> 00:11:29,439
Yes.

224
00:11:30,356 --> 00:11:31,900
- She makes more.
- Ah…

225
00:11:31,983 --> 00:11:33,401
- Spot-on.
- It's true. She does.

226
00:11:33,484 --> 00:11:34,819
Definitely.

227
00:11:34,903 --> 00:11:36,321
There's a chance

228
00:11:36,404 --> 00:11:39,782
you might end up taking care of him
like he's your son.

229
00:11:42,202 --> 00:11:43,203
My gosh.

230
00:11:44,204 --> 00:11:45,288
"Like a son"?

231
00:11:46,664 --> 00:11:50,210
- Actually, here's what I want to know.
- Okay.

232
00:11:50,793 --> 00:11:52,420
- It's about my husband.
- Yes?

233
00:11:52,503 --> 00:11:54,547
Will he marry a second time?

234
00:11:54,631 --> 00:11:56,716
Will he marry a second time?

235
00:11:56,799 --> 00:11:58,468
- Remarry?
- Yes, will he?

236
00:11:59,636 --> 00:12:01,721
- What?
- Where did that come from?

237
00:12:01,804 --> 00:12:03,473
Why would she ask…

238
00:12:04,557 --> 00:12:05,808
Oh.

239
00:12:05,892 --> 00:12:08,937
- Will Hong Hyegul remarry?
- Huh? What is she trying to ask?

240
00:12:09,020 --> 00:12:10,230
This is shocking.

241
00:12:11,314 --> 00:12:13,358
That's a scandalous question, isn't it?

242
00:12:13,441 --> 00:12:16,444
To ask if her own husband
will marry a different woman…

243
00:12:17,612 --> 00:12:19,614
- It's unprecedented.
- What the heck?

244
00:12:20,782 --> 00:12:23,034
Why ask if her husband will remarry?

245
00:12:23,743 --> 00:12:25,578
Why? Do you want a divorce?

246
00:12:25,662 --> 00:12:27,622
No, I don't want a divorce.

247
00:12:27,705 --> 00:12:30,792
Some people ask that
if they're terminally ill.

248
00:12:30,875 --> 00:12:32,335
Is she unwell?

249
00:12:32,418 --> 00:12:34,420
No, she seems healthy.

250
00:12:35,380 --> 00:12:37,257
This is such a shocking question.

251
00:12:38,508 --> 00:12:41,886
Is your husband fated to remarry?

252
00:12:42,762 --> 00:12:44,931
- That's your question, right?
- Yes.

253
00:12:54,357 --> 00:12:56,234
Well, the cards do show

254
00:12:56,317 --> 00:12:57,986
your husband facing outward.

255
00:12:58,069 --> 00:12:59,362
Oh!

256
00:12:59,445 --> 00:13:01,364
- Huh?
- Hmm?

257
00:13:01,447 --> 00:13:04,867
That means there's a possibility
he might get interested in other women.

258
00:13:04,951 --> 00:13:06,703
- Uh-huh.
- He may get interested,

259
00:13:06,786 --> 00:13:08,871
but he won't leave the house.

260
00:13:10,581 --> 00:13:12,458
He just looks outside from home.

261
00:13:12,542 --> 00:13:14,627
- He's just looking outside?
- That's right.

262
00:13:15,753 --> 00:13:18,631
He sees them through a medium like a TV.

263
00:13:18,715 --> 00:13:23,011
But him going outside, meeting someone,
and getting remarried?

264
00:13:23,094 --> 00:13:24,595
I don't think that's likely.

265
00:13:27,682 --> 00:13:29,600
Why does she look so disappointed?

266
00:13:30,351 --> 00:13:31,686
Yeah, why isn't she happy?

267
00:13:35,398 --> 00:13:36,441
This man

268
00:13:37,025 --> 00:13:39,861
goes all the way with his first love.

269
00:13:43,698 --> 00:13:45,116
Look at the cards here.

270
00:13:45,199 --> 00:13:47,326
He meets someone at a young age.

271
00:13:47,410 --> 00:13:49,829
And they make a promise to each other.

272
00:13:49,912 --> 00:13:51,748
"Let's stay together."

273
00:13:51,831 --> 00:13:54,333
The last card says,

274
00:13:54,417 --> 00:13:56,335
"Even if we break up,
we'll get back together."

275
00:13:57,045 --> 00:13:58,546
- Ah…
- So,

276
00:13:58,629 --> 00:14:02,175
this present life is not the first time
you've met each other.

277
00:14:02,759 --> 00:14:04,719
You've met in your past lives,

278
00:14:04,802 --> 00:14:08,556
you 2 are together in this life,
and you'll meet again in the next life.

279
00:14:11,601 --> 00:14:13,061
So if you ask me if a man like this

280
00:14:13,144 --> 00:14:15,646
would remarry, I don't think so.

281
00:14:16,689 --> 00:14:17,690
I see.

282
00:14:20,193 --> 00:14:21,778
She looks devastated.

283
00:14:22,570 --> 00:14:23,905
Why does she look so glum?

284
00:14:25,073 --> 00:14:27,116
Does she want to divorce him
when she's older?

285
00:14:27,200 --> 00:14:28,326
It's a mystery.

286
00:14:29,952 --> 00:14:31,537
The time is up.

287
00:14:31,621 --> 00:14:33,289
- Thanks.
- Thank you.

288
00:14:36,918 --> 00:14:39,295
Monad is a very skilled tarot master,

289
00:14:40,797 --> 00:14:43,091
but today, my Granny spirit
didn't clock out.

290
00:14:43,174 --> 00:14:45,051
She was right by my side.

291
00:14:45,134 --> 00:14:46,594
So I was pretty confident.

292
00:14:50,306 --> 00:14:51,557
Lee Sobin,

293
00:14:51,641 --> 00:14:53,476
please begin your reading.

294
00:15:19,377 --> 00:15:20,670
Well, Dr. Lyuh.

295
00:15:22,713 --> 00:15:25,049
You're someone who doesn't like studying.

296
00:15:25,133 --> 00:15:26,884
So how do you keep doing it?

297
00:15:29,470 --> 00:15:31,764
Studying isn't your thing…

298
00:15:31,848 --> 00:15:33,850
…and it's possible you even hate it,

299
00:15:33,933 --> 00:15:36,686
so it's so interesting
that you keep at it.

300
00:15:36,769 --> 00:15:37,770
Oh.

301
00:15:38,646 --> 00:15:41,065
You're right. I don't like studying.

302
00:15:41,149 --> 00:15:43,734
- Right.
- But luckily, I was born smart.

303
00:15:43,818 --> 00:15:45,778
I'd study
just for a few days before exams,

304
00:15:45,862 --> 00:15:47,280
and I was still top of my class.

305
00:15:50,032 --> 00:15:52,451
After just 4 days of studying?
She's a genius.

306
00:15:52,535 --> 00:15:55,246
- She's just born smart.
- She was. It's not about effort.

307
00:15:55,329 --> 00:15:57,498
Earlier, you called yourself
"Good Luck Esther."

308
00:15:57,582 --> 00:15:59,208
- Yes.
- It might be because

309
00:15:59,292 --> 00:16:01,419
you experienced all the misfortune
when you were young.

310
00:16:03,796 --> 00:16:05,965
You experienced all the bad things in life

311
00:16:06,048 --> 00:16:09,260
before you turned 14 or 15.

312
00:16:09,343 --> 00:16:11,721
That's why things
are comfortable for you now.

313
00:16:11,804 --> 00:16:13,097
Yes, that's true.

314
00:16:13,890 --> 00:16:15,349
- Oh, she's right?
- Oh…

315
00:16:15,433 --> 00:16:17,518
- Oh.
- She's right.

316
00:16:17,602 --> 00:16:20,354
Yes, she was deported to Japan.

317
00:16:20,438 --> 00:16:21,647
1973, AGED 9,

318
00:16:21,731 --> 00:16:23,399
HER FATHER ARRESTED BY THE KCIA
AND THE FAMILY DEPORTED TO JAPAN

319
00:16:23,482 --> 00:16:25,318
She experienced
all the misfortune before 14?

320
00:16:25,401 --> 00:16:26,819
- That's true.
- Yes.

321
00:16:26,903 --> 00:16:28,279
Since then, she did well in school.

322
00:16:28,362 --> 00:16:29,363
Yes.

323
00:16:29,447 --> 00:16:32,241
When the whole thing with her father
ended, she became top of class.

324
00:16:32,325 --> 00:16:33,326
Yes.

325
00:16:33,868 --> 00:16:36,078
Now, what my Granny spirit
keeps saying is,

326
00:16:36,162 --> 00:16:39,290
"You have a husband, but you don't.
What's going on?"

327
00:16:39,832 --> 00:16:43,044
You do have a husband. He's there.

328
00:16:43,127 --> 00:16:45,546
But you're somewhere in between
being married and being strangers.

329
00:16:46,297 --> 00:16:47,840
Gosh.

330
00:16:52,303 --> 00:16:54,347
It must be tough, but the problem is,

331
00:16:54,430 --> 00:16:56,474
he has no intention of leaving you.

332
00:16:56,557 --> 00:16:58,142
Just stay together.

333
00:16:58,226 --> 00:17:02,146
Keep him around,
but separate your individual spaces.

334
00:17:02,230 --> 00:17:05,566
-That might be for the better.
-Okay.

335
00:17:05,650 --> 00:17:07,568
Because you're not compatible.

336
00:17:12,740 --> 00:17:13,991
Oh, no.

337
00:17:14,075 --> 00:17:16,369
It's mentioned in the file.

338
00:17:16,452 --> 00:17:19,372
-Her husband lived on Jeju-do alone.
-Oh…

339
00:17:19,455 --> 00:17:20,581
Yeah, he moved there.

340
00:17:20,665 --> 00:17:21,791
HER HUSBAND MOVED
TO JEJU-DO BY HIMSELF

341
00:17:21,874 --> 00:17:24,502
Here's another thing
my Granny spirit keeps saying.

342
00:17:24,585 --> 00:17:27,672
You say, "A lot of people will like me.
They will love me."

343
00:17:27,755 --> 00:17:29,507
"I'm fine."

344
00:17:29,590 --> 00:17:30,925
But she says you feel lonely.

345
00:17:31,634 --> 00:17:33,511
She's lonely?

346
00:17:33,594 --> 00:17:34,887
- Oh…
- She feels lonely.

347
00:17:34,971 --> 00:17:37,223
Although I'm a medical doctor myself,

348
00:17:38,099 --> 00:17:39,559
I've struggled with

349
00:17:40,059 --> 00:17:41,769
long-term depression

350
00:17:41,852 --> 00:17:44,814
that's been hard to overcome.

351
00:17:44,897 --> 00:17:48,150
I've been suffering from it
since high school, actually.

352
00:17:49,026 --> 00:17:50,403
Oh…

353
00:17:51,654 --> 00:17:52,738
Mmm…

354
00:17:52,822 --> 00:17:53,990
Oh, dear.

355
00:17:54,073 --> 00:17:55,575
But she's so cheerful.

356
00:17:58,202 --> 00:17:59,203
Actually…

357
00:18:01,205 --> 00:18:03,791
My beloved younger sister

358
00:18:04,375 --> 00:18:09,088
died a very lonely death 9 years ago.

359
00:18:10,590 --> 00:18:12,174
Ah…

360
00:18:13,259 --> 00:18:14,969
Ah…

361
00:18:19,307 --> 00:18:21,809
After she died,

362
00:18:21,892 --> 00:18:24,729
I was absolutely devastated,

363
00:18:25,313 --> 00:18:30,484
but my business was thriving,
and things were going well for my kids.

364
00:18:34,113 --> 00:18:35,698
Yes, her spirit is helping you.

365
00:18:36,616 --> 00:18:37,950
Right.

366
00:18:40,161 --> 00:18:42,538
Whenever something bad was about
to happen to you,

367
00:18:42,622 --> 00:18:45,499
and whenever you were about
to get swayed by negativity,

368
00:18:46,208 --> 00:18:48,878
you had a way out just in time

369
00:18:48,961 --> 00:18:50,671
because she's looking out for you.

370
00:18:58,804 --> 00:19:00,056
Oh, dear.

371
00:19:01,641 --> 00:19:03,601
Oh…

372
00:19:04,143 --> 00:19:05,436
Oh…

373
00:19:12,860 --> 00:19:13,861
Okay.

374
00:19:13,944 --> 00:19:16,656
Don't bottle things up.

375
00:19:16,739 --> 00:19:19,700
It's okay to miss her.

376
00:19:22,036 --> 00:19:23,162
It's okay to feel bad.

377
00:19:29,126 --> 00:19:31,712
But don't think
that you failed to protect her.

378
00:19:31,796 --> 00:19:33,339
Because that's not true.

379
00:19:36,092 --> 00:19:38,219
But I do think I failed to protect her.

380
00:19:42,973 --> 00:19:45,893
- Oh, dear.
- Mmm…

381
00:19:56,320 --> 00:19:57,363
It's okay.

382
00:20:00,491 --> 00:20:03,494
Because of what happened to my sister,

383
00:20:04,120 --> 00:20:05,788
my depression got worse.

384
00:20:07,998 --> 00:20:12,420
It became even harder
to treat it after her death.

385
00:20:13,254 --> 00:20:16,549
I was hospitalized many times

386
00:20:16,632 --> 00:20:17,967
for electroconvulsive therapy

387
00:20:18,050 --> 00:20:19,635
to shock my brain.

388
00:20:19,719 --> 00:20:20,720
Huh?

389
00:20:22,888 --> 00:20:24,598
What is this supposed to mean?

390
00:20:25,474 --> 00:20:27,309
Electric shocks… to the brain?

391
00:20:28,185 --> 00:20:32,773
Perhaps, to stimulate an area
to dull the senses?

392
00:20:32,857 --> 00:20:34,442
Oh, to dull the senses.

393
00:20:34,525 --> 00:20:36,318
Her depression

394
00:20:36,402 --> 00:20:38,696
might be a lot more severe than we think.

395
00:20:40,489 --> 00:20:43,617
The treatment caused
a bit of memory loss too.

396
00:20:44,744 --> 00:20:46,454
And with everything going on,

397
00:20:46,537 --> 00:20:50,249
I don't really want to live that long.

398
00:20:50,332 --> 00:20:51,542
Oh, no.

399
00:20:54,628 --> 00:20:57,339
I feel terrible for my family,
saying this, but…

400
00:20:59,633 --> 00:21:00,968
Don't even think about it.

401
00:21:07,975 --> 00:21:09,226
I'm always

402
00:21:09,810 --> 00:21:11,896
thinking about when my last day will be.

403
00:21:14,899 --> 00:21:16,442
What did she just say?

404
00:21:20,863 --> 00:21:23,991
"Do I have to live in such pain?"

405
00:21:25,075 --> 00:21:27,495
"November 18. That will be my last day."

406
00:21:30,414 --> 00:21:33,250
It's not the birthday
of any member of my family.

407
00:21:33,334 --> 00:21:37,713
If it were Christmas, for example,
my family would be sad every Christmas.

408
00:21:38,214 --> 00:21:40,090
Ah.

409
00:21:40,174 --> 00:21:41,175
Oh.

410
00:21:41,258 --> 00:21:42,802
- Ugh.
- Oh…

411
00:21:45,179 --> 00:21:46,347
Look here.

412
00:21:47,515 --> 00:21:48,557
Yes.

413
00:21:48,641 --> 00:21:50,100
CONSIDERING
ASSISTED DEATH OVERSEAS

414
00:21:50,184 --> 00:21:52,853
Medically assisted death is allowed
in some countries.

415
00:21:52,937 --> 00:21:54,814
Switzerland, for example.

416
00:21:54,897 --> 00:21:56,565
She can die with dignity.

417
00:21:57,983 --> 00:21:59,735
I wanted to choose a day that didn't clash

418
00:21:59,819 --> 00:22:03,697
with any special days
for the family or celebrations.

419
00:22:03,781 --> 00:22:04,865
But then…

420
00:22:05,533 --> 00:22:08,744
I thought I shouldn't go
before this show airs,

421
00:22:08,828 --> 00:22:11,288
so I put it off until next year.

422
00:22:11,372 --> 00:22:13,249
Keep putting it off every year like that.

423
00:22:13,332 --> 00:22:15,960
You still love your work.

424
00:22:16,043 --> 00:22:18,587
You love your work,
and you're responsible.

425
00:22:18,671 --> 00:22:19,922
Keep going with that strength.

426
00:22:20,005 --> 00:22:21,340
- Okay.
- To be honest,

427
00:22:21,423 --> 00:22:24,593
I say this because I don't think
you'll want to keep going for your family.

428
00:22:27,930 --> 00:22:29,390
You think you've done your part for them.

429
00:22:29,473 --> 00:22:30,474
That's true.

430
00:22:30,558 --> 00:22:33,060
You got them where they want to be.

431
00:22:33,644 --> 00:22:35,312
You've provided everything they need.

432
00:22:35,396 --> 00:22:37,773
But you still want to achieve more
with your work.

433
00:22:37,857 --> 00:22:38,858
Right.

434
00:22:38,941 --> 00:22:41,026
I want you to keep living on for that.

435
00:22:42,403 --> 00:22:45,030
Your reading was very accurate.

436
00:22:45,114 --> 00:22:48,117
I'm the type to prepare in advance.

437
00:22:48,200 --> 00:22:50,369
I've already prepared everything

438
00:22:50,452 --> 00:22:53,330
my husband and children would need
after I'm gone.

439
00:22:56,917 --> 00:22:58,294
In that process,

440
00:22:58,377 --> 00:23:00,921
I made plans for everyone.

441
00:23:01,005 --> 00:23:05,175
Every member of my family,
my staff, even my housekeeper,

442
00:23:05,259 --> 00:23:07,636
I've made sure they can live on
even when I'm gone.

443
00:23:07,720 --> 00:23:08,888
Oh…

444
00:23:08,971 --> 00:23:11,557
Her company provides
really good benefits to the employees.

445
00:23:11,640 --> 00:23:13,976
She even bought an employee
a home in Cheongdam-dong.

446
00:23:14,059 --> 00:23:17,646
She plans to buy
her housekeeper an apartment.

447
00:23:17,730 --> 00:23:20,941
- For her staff and…
- That's incredible.

448
00:23:21,025 --> 00:23:23,569
Depression has its ups and downs.

449
00:23:23,652 --> 00:23:25,779
When I feel down, I go,

450
00:23:25,863 --> 00:23:27,114
"I've done everything."

451
00:23:27,197 --> 00:23:29,825
I've already prepared
everything for everyone.

452
00:23:30,492 --> 00:23:33,954
I don't want to live in misery.
When I wake up in the morning…

453
00:23:34,622 --> 00:23:37,875
-You just want to end it.
-That's right.

454
00:23:41,128 --> 00:23:42,630
Ah.

455
00:23:42,713 --> 00:23:45,341
She thinks she's done all she can
for her family.

456
00:23:49,678 --> 00:23:52,723
I asked her something earlier.

457
00:23:52,806 --> 00:23:56,685
- If my husband would ever remarry.
- Hmm.

458
00:23:56,769 --> 00:23:58,437
If the answer had been yes--

459
00:23:58,520 --> 00:24:01,065
-It would have meant you'd die.
-Yes, it would have meant I'd be gone.

460
00:24:01,690 --> 00:24:03,943
That's why I asked her that.

461
00:24:04,693 --> 00:24:06,862
- That's why she asked.
- Yes.

462
00:24:06,946 --> 00:24:08,864
If he'd marry someone else,
she could let him go.

463
00:24:10,032 --> 00:24:11,075
Because she'd leave.

464
00:24:11,158 --> 00:24:14,912
She wants him to meet
a good woman because she'll be gone.

465
00:24:14,995 --> 00:24:16,664
Which year was your husband born?

466
00:24:16,747 --> 00:24:18,666
- In 1967.
- In 1967.

467
00:24:28,300 --> 00:24:29,677
Wait.

468
00:24:29,760 --> 00:24:31,720
Is 1 of you the other person's first love?

469
00:24:32,888 --> 00:24:33,931
I'm asking

470
00:24:35,057 --> 00:24:39,144
because I'm getting that either you're
his first love or he's yours.

471
00:24:40,145 --> 00:24:42,022
Gosh, her husband.

472
00:24:42,106 --> 00:24:43,816
She's her husband's first love.

473
00:24:43,899 --> 00:24:45,693
- He never dated anyone else.
- He didn't.

474
00:24:45,776 --> 00:24:47,111
So she's his first love?

475
00:24:47,778 --> 00:24:49,363
He'd never dated anyone before.

476
00:24:49,446 --> 00:24:50,906
I had no idea.

477
00:24:52,282 --> 00:24:53,784
Wow, this is crazy.

478
00:24:53,867 --> 00:24:55,411
She can see that?

479
00:24:55,995 --> 00:24:57,371
Looks like she can.

480
00:24:57,454 --> 00:25:00,541
I'm likely my husband's first love…

481
00:25:00,624 --> 00:25:02,042
- And the first woman he'd ever dated.
- Yes.

482
00:25:02,126 --> 00:25:04,253
Until he met me,

483
00:25:04,837 --> 00:25:07,589
he'd never even kissed a woman.

484
00:25:08,215 --> 00:25:11,010
My goodness. He had never…

485
00:25:11,093 --> 00:25:13,137
Hong Hyegul, my husband…

486
00:25:13,220 --> 00:25:15,222
He's so kind and considerate,

487
00:25:15,305 --> 00:25:17,641
but he's not like an ordinary person.

488
00:25:19,143 --> 00:25:22,730
A few days ago,
he went to a water park on his own.

489
00:25:23,439 --> 00:25:24,440
I see.

490
00:25:24,523 --> 00:25:26,442
He posted selfies of himself.

491
00:25:27,401 --> 00:25:28,777
What? On his own?

492
00:25:30,070 --> 00:25:32,573
- Oh, my gosh.
- At a water park…

493
00:25:33,198 --> 00:25:36,201
But it was too crowded, so he went
to the amusement park next door,

494
00:25:36,285 --> 00:25:40,539
went to the safari,
and fed the giraffes and stuff.

495
00:25:41,081 --> 00:25:44,293
He lives in his own little world.

496
00:25:44,376 --> 00:25:46,628
He does things like that all the time.

497
00:25:47,296 --> 00:25:50,507
- He's lonely too. They're both lonely.
- You're right.

498
00:25:52,217 --> 00:25:55,095
I just don't understand him.

499
00:25:55,179 --> 00:25:58,348
I doubt anyone can understand him.

500
00:25:59,099 --> 00:26:00,559
Only he understands himself.

501
00:26:01,643 --> 00:26:05,606
It may look like he lives in his own world
and all he cares about is his happiness,

502
00:26:05,689 --> 00:26:07,066
but he's really lonely too.

503
00:26:08,358 --> 00:26:09,860
- My husband?
- Yes.

504
00:26:12,279 --> 00:26:13,781
This is the last love.

505
00:26:14,573 --> 00:26:15,657
Whose last love?

506
00:26:15,741 --> 00:26:17,409
- I'm his last love?
- Yes.

507
00:26:17,493 --> 00:26:18,535
So just give up.

508
00:26:19,036 --> 00:26:21,038
He won't find anyone else.

509
00:26:22,748 --> 00:26:23,749
One more thing.

510
00:26:25,834 --> 00:26:27,586
Hang in there for just 2 more years.

511
00:26:28,754 --> 00:26:29,838
-Two years.
-Right.

512
00:26:29,922 --> 00:26:31,507
In 2 years,

513
00:26:31,590 --> 00:26:33,967
your depression will get much better.

514
00:26:34,551 --> 00:26:36,011
Ah.

515
00:26:36,095 --> 00:26:38,639
The end of 2027 and 2028.

516
00:26:38,722 --> 00:26:43,852
I keep hearing happy laughter
from around that time.

517
00:26:43,936 --> 00:26:46,980
- Ah, around that time…
- Yes.

518
00:26:47,064 --> 00:26:49,274
…maybe I'll have grandchildren.

519
00:26:49,358 --> 00:26:51,360
That's possible. I hear laughter.

520
00:26:52,069 --> 00:26:55,072
- If she holds on for 2 more years? Yes.
- Oh…

521
00:26:55,155 --> 00:26:56,323
Two more years.

522
00:26:57,241 --> 00:26:59,660
Yes, hang in there for 2 years.

523
00:27:00,160 --> 00:27:04,832
If your Granny spirit says
things will get better in 2 years…

524
00:27:04,915 --> 00:27:07,543
- Hold on. Hang in there until then.
- Huh?

525
00:27:09,086 --> 00:27:12,047
Okay, I won't pick out any more dates.

526
00:27:15,134 --> 00:27:16,927
Yes, that's what we wanted to hear.

527
00:27:17,511 --> 00:27:18,720
It is.

528
00:27:24,726 --> 00:27:27,062
Can I feel your hand, Doctor?

529
00:27:29,898 --> 00:27:31,567
Out of the blue?

530
00:27:52,254 --> 00:27:53,255
You're fine,

531
00:27:53,338 --> 00:27:55,257
but where is your late father resting?

532
00:27:58,135 --> 00:28:00,387
Did you move him?

533
00:28:02,306 --> 00:28:03,473
Huh?

534
00:28:05,475 --> 00:28:07,019
I'm getting that he was moved.

535
00:28:08,186 --> 00:28:09,563
Yes, we moved his grave.

536
00:28:09,646 --> 00:28:11,690
Huh?

537
00:28:11,773 --> 00:28:13,650
- Ah…
- Really?

538
00:28:13,734 --> 00:28:15,110
She figured that out?

539
00:28:17,237 --> 00:28:19,448
Well, about that…

540
00:28:23,118 --> 00:28:25,078
After you moved his grave,

541
00:28:25,162 --> 00:28:27,080
your family must've struggled a bit.

542
00:28:27,664 --> 00:28:30,876
- Right.
- I'll be honest. Around that time.

543
00:28:32,044 --> 00:28:33,253
The grave's a problem?

544
00:28:35,172 --> 00:28:39,635
It's like he went from living in a house
with a garden to an apartment.

545
00:28:39,718 --> 00:28:41,637
It's a little stuffy for him.

546
00:28:41,720 --> 00:28:43,472
He's not exactly happy.

547
00:28:43,555 --> 00:28:46,433
He was buried in our family gravesite,

548
00:28:46,516 --> 00:28:48,644
but we moved his urn
to a nearby columbarium.

549
00:28:51,772 --> 00:28:53,273
Wow.

550
00:28:53,357 --> 00:28:55,150
Really?

551
00:28:56,777 --> 00:28:58,779
So he's uncomfortable there?

552
00:29:00,364 --> 00:29:03,825
He wanted to rest comfortably on his land,

553
00:29:03,909 --> 00:29:06,161
but where he is now is
a bit stuffy for him.

554
00:29:06,244 --> 00:29:09,164
-Visit him often, and he'll be fine.
-Okay.

555
00:29:09,247 --> 00:29:11,375
I will go to see him more often.

556
00:29:13,543 --> 00:29:15,545
I just wanted to hold her hand.

557
00:29:17,464 --> 00:29:20,717
I think it was her father
that wanted to hold his daughter's hand.

558
00:29:22,636 --> 00:29:25,472
He held his little girl's hand
through me for a moment.

559
00:29:29,559 --> 00:29:31,645
The time is up.

560
00:29:32,646 --> 00:29:37,067
You've always looked so bubbly
and bright on TV, Dr. Lyuh.

561
00:29:37,150 --> 00:29:40,445
You give off positive energy
and make us smile,

562
00:29:40,529 --> 00:29:44,199
so I think many will be shocked
to hear what you said today.

563
00:29:44,282 --> 00:29:45,283
Ah… Ah…

564
00:29:45,867 --> 00:29:49,121
- I am indeed a bright and cheerful person.
- Hmm.

565
00:29:49,204 --> 00:29:50,789
- I was born that way.
- Okay.

566
00:29:50,872 --> 00:29:54,251
Depression is an illness
I'm suffering from.

567
00:29:54,334 --> 00:29:56,211
Yes. Yes.

568
00:29:56,294 --> 00:29:59,798
So I feel down
and melancholy when I'm alone.

569
00:29:59,881 --> 00:30:03,385
When I'm around others,
I laugh and have a good time.

570
00:30:04,011 --> 00:30:06,054
Many people are like me.

571
00:30:06,138 --> 00:30:09,766
I'm telling you all this

572
00:30:10,434 --> 00:30:13,770
because I want to let people know
they're not the only ones suffering.

573
00:30:13,854 --> 00:30:15,272
I want them to know that.

574
00:30:15,981 --> 00:30:17,107
Hmm.

575
00:30:19,985 --> 00:30:23,196
Speaking with you guys today

576
00:30:23,280 --> 00:30:26,658
felt like a session with a psychiatrist.

577
00:30:28,285 --> 00:30:30,078
When I go to see a psychiatrist,

578
00:30:30,162 --> 00:30:33,623
they're mostly my friends from med school,
so I can't really open up.

579
00:30:33,707 --> 00:30:34,708
Ah…

580
00:30:34,791 --> 00:30:36,418
- That's why she's here.
- Yes.

581
00:30:36,501 --> 00:30:40,881
I get it. It can be worrying
if you know them.

582
00:30:43,008 --> 00:30:45,052
I can't say how I really feel.

583
00:30:45,135 --> 00:30:49,181
When it comes to mental illness,

584
00:30:50,432 --> 00:30:55,145
you need to be able to say
what pains you and gain empathy.

585
00:30:55,228 --> 00:30:58,315
And coming here and speaking to you all

586
00:30:58,398 --> 00:31:02,235
really comforted me and cheered me up.

587
00:31:02,319 --> 00:31:05,197
They're such a positive impact on her.

588
00:31:07,657 --> 00:31:10,077
I'd like to ask you something, Doctor.

589
00:31:10,160 --> 00:31:13,163
You said something that made us think
you were considering

590
00:31:13,246 --> 00:31:15,165
-medically assisted death.
-Yes.

591
00:31:15,248 --> 00:31:17,709
I'm wondering

592
00:31:18,460 --> 00:31:21,296
if today's experience has changed

593
00:31:22,130 --> 00:31:24,508
how you feel about it in any way.

594
00:31:25,926 --> 00:31:29,054
Today, I was told
good things would happen in 2 years.

595
00:31:29,137 --> 00:31:32,849
Now I'm thinking I should stick around
for my younger son's wedding.

596
00:31:32,933 --> 00:31:35,936
And I think I'll live to be 90 years old
before I know it.

597
00:31:37,854 --> 00:31:39,439
- That sounds good.
- Yes.

598
00:31:39,523 --> 00:31:41,525
-Keep putting it off.
-I agree.

599
00:31:46,488 --> 00:31:48,365
The Battle of Gods.

600
00:31:48,448 --> 00:31:50,575
The second match is over.

601
00:31:51,368 --> 00:31:54,371
Lyuh Esther and Fate Reapers.

602
00:31:54,454 --> 00:31:55,580
Between Monad

603
00:31:57,165 --> 00:31:58,208
and Lee Sobin…

604
00:32:00,460 --> 00:32:02,504
choose the survivor.

605
00:32:03,797 --> 00:32:05,006
They must be nervous.

606
00:32:05,090 --> 00:32:06,174
THE BATTLE OF GODS RULE:

607
00:32:06,258 --> 00:32:08,343
THE CLIENT AND EACH FATE REAPER
HAS ONE VOTE EACH

608
00:32:08,426 --> 00:32:10,720
- I'm so torn.
- I don't know anymore either.

609
00:32:10,804 --> 00:32:12,722
This is hard. What should I do?

610
00:32:16,476 --> 00:32:18,395
The Battle of Gods.

611
00:32:18,478 --> 00:32:21,481
Here goes the result of the second match.

612
00:32:22,149 --> 00:32:23,275
My gosh.

613
00:32:23,900 --> 00:32:25,068
I'm so nervous!

614
00:32:30,949 --> 00:32:32,826
I thought that if I trusted
in my Granny spirit,

615
00:32:32,909 --> 00:32:35,996
I could win. I was confident.

616
00:32:37,581 --> 00:32:38,957
I'm so close to winning it all.

617
00:32:39,040 --> 00:32:41,376
I got this far.
I might as well go all the way!

618
00:32:43,128 --> 00:32:46,506
This is Lyuh Esther's choice.

619
00:32:48,258 --> 00:32:49,926
MONAD

620
00:32:50,010 --> 00:32:51,469
Oh!

621
00:32:54,181 --> 00:32:55,182
Me?

622
00:32:59,186 --> 00:33:02,314
And here are the Fate Reapers' choices.

623
00:33:03,773 --> 00:33:04,983
LEE SOBIN

624
00:33:12,282 --> 00:33:14,618
LEE SOBIN

625
00:33:14,701 --> 00:33:15,702
The survivor is…

626
00:33:15,785 --> 00:33:17,537
Lee Sobin.

627
00:33:18,205 --> 00:33:19,623
- Congratulations.
- Congratulations.

628
00:33:19,706 --> 00:33:20,707
LEE SOBIN SURVIVES

629
00:33:20,790 --> 00:33:22,542
Congratulations.

630
00:33:26,838 --> 00:33:31,551
Dr. Lyuh, may I ask why you chose Monad?

631
00:33:31,635 --> 00:33:32,844
Honestly,

632
00:33:32,928 --> 00:33:35,722
I'm very grateful to Sobin,

633
00:33:35,805 --> 00:33:38,016
and to Monad too.

634
00:33:38,600 --> 00:33:41,728
When it came to interpreting
the tarot cards,

635
00:33:41,811 --> 00:33:44,147
she was very trustworthy

636
00:33:44,231 --> 00:33:47,776
and what she said was quite convincing.

637
00:33:47,859 --> 00:33:50,111
I had no idea that tarot reading

638
00:33:50,195 --> 00:33:53,657
could go into such detail
and resonate with me.

639
00:33:53,740 --> 00:33:55,825
I really liked her advice too.

640
00:33:57,994 --> 00:34:01,581
Monad's Battle of Fates ends here.

641
00:34:03,625 --> 00:34:07,420
It takes me 2.5 hours to get here.

642
00:34:07,504 --> 00:34:09,923
There's a song I listen to on the way.

643
00:34:10,924 --> 00:34:14,302
It's You Move Me by PSY.

644
00:34:14,386 --> 00:34:15,387
The lyrics say…

645
00:34:15,470 --> 00:34:18,306
…"My life is spectacular."

646
00:34:18,390 --> 00:34:20,976
"Without the stage,

647
00:34:21,059 --> 00:34:23,645
my life would be
like a spring day without flowers."

648
00:34:24,312 --> 00:34:26,106
To me, this stage…

649
00:34:36,616 --> 00:34:37,784
Oh.

650
00:34:39,119 --> 00:34:40,120
Oh, dear.

651
00:34:46,459 --> 00:34:50,672
There's no way I could beat a shaman

652
00:34:50,755 --> 00:34:53,008
who gives a reading through deities.

653
00:34:53,091 --> 00:34:55,093
My intuition is all I've got.

654
00:34:55,719 --> 00:34:59,472
I feel like I was gifted a spring day
in full bloom through this stage.

655
00:34:59,556 --> 00:35:00,807
So I'm so happy.

656
00:35:02,559 --> 00:35:04,436
I'll root for you until the very end.

657
00:35:10,525 --> 00:35:11,526
Gosh.

658
00:35:12,235 --> 00:35:15,196
- They're all so well-spoken.
- Such nice words.

659
00:35:15,280 --> 00:35:17,532
It's nice how they root for each other.

660
00:35:23,371 --> 00:35:26,625
I was sad to think
I won't get to see her again.

661
00:35:26,708 --> 00:35:28,543
That's why I cried so much.

662
00:35:28,627 --> 00:35:30,629
But I made it this far,

663
00:35:30,712 --> 00:35:32,422
so I plan to keep charging on.

664
00:35:34,883 --> 00:35:38,928
Six Fate Readers fight
in the Battle of Gods.

665
00:35:39,721 --> 00:35:43,224
Let the third match begin.

666
00:35:44,059 --> 00:35:46,353
Gosh, we only have these 2 people left.

667
00:35:46,436 --> 00:35:47,854
- This should be fun.
- My gosh.

668
00:35:47,937 --> 00:35:49,147
I'm so excited.

669
00:35:49,731 --> 00:35:51,858
I don't mind who I go up against.

670
00:35:51,941 --> 00:35:54,944
I'll just say what I see and feel.

671
00:35:55,445 --> 00:35:58,448
I was going to do my reading
through my deities.

672
00:35:58,531 --> 00:35:59,908
So I was confident.

673
00:36:00,492 --> 00:36:02,243
Gosh, even I'm nervous now.

674
00:36:03,495 --> 00:36:06,039
Here is the person
you will do a reading for.

675
00:36:07,207 --> 00:36:08,458
BORN ON JULY 3, 1983, FEMALE

676
00:36:08,541 --> 00:36:11,336
- Born in 1983.
- It's a woman.

677
00:36:11,920 --> 00:36:13,296
The Year of the Pig.

678
00:36:13,880 --> 00:36:15,048
What a tough life.

679
00:36:15,757 --> 00:36:17,050
Who is it?

680
00:36:23,932 --> 00:36:25,266
Who is it?

681
00:36:26,309 --> 00:36:27,769
Who's coming?

682
00:36:34,693 --> 00:36:36,069
Oh.

683
00:36:36,152 --> 00:36:37,153
Gosh.

684
00:36:43,993 --> 00:36:44,994
What?

685
00:36:45,078 --> 00:36:46,871
Isn't she the chef?

686
00:36:46,955 --> 00:36:48,623
- Chef Jung!
- Isn't that Jung Jisun?

687
00:36:49,207 --> 00:36:50,291
It's Chef Jung Jisun.

688
00:36:50,875 --> 00:36:52,210
Famous for sweet and crispy
sweet potatoes.

689
00:36:54,129 --> 00:36:56,131
- Culinary Class Wars!
- Yes.

690
00:37:02,762 --> 00:37:05,223
THE SWEET-AND-CRISPY
SWEET POTATOES MAKER

691
00:37:05,306 --> 00:37:07,392
WHO THRILLED THE WORLD

692
00:37:07,767 --> 00:37:09,686
CULINARY CLASS WARS
SHOOTS JUNG TO STARDOM

693
00:37:09,769 --> 00:37:12,230
WORLD-CLASS CHEF JUNG JISUN
SPEAKS AT HARVARD

694
00:37:12,313 --> 00:37:15,316
- Ah… Hello.
- Oh… It's great to see you.

695
00:37:15,400 --> 00:37:17,026
Chef Jung Jisun is…

696
00:37:17,110 --> 00:37:19,529
She's the busiest chef in all of Korea.

697
00:37:19,612 --> 00:37:20,739
You're right.

698
00:37:20,822 --> 00:37:23,074
I know her pretty well.

699
00:37:23,158 --> 00:37:24,659
You guys are close.

700
00:37:24,743 --> 00:37:27,203
It's kind of surprising
that you go to see fortune-tellers.

701
00:37:27,287 --> 00:37:29,080
Ah…

702
00:37:29,164 --> 00:37:32,208
Do you often
go to see fortune-tellers?

703
00:37:32,292 --> 00:37:34,794
Before I started
my large-scale business,

704
00:37:34,878 --> 00:37:36,713
I went to many saju readers.

705
00:37:36,796 --> 00:37:38,173
Oh…

706
00:37:38,256 --> 00:37:42,260
I was a bit too afraid
to go to a shaman.

707
00:37:42,802 --> 00:37:45,555
I guess it's because I've never tried it.

708
00:37:46,514 --> 00:37:47,515
That's true.

709
00:37:48,224 --> 00:37:51,186
Seeing a shaman for the first time
can be a bit scary, for sure.

710
00:37:51,269 --> 00:37:52,353
- It is.
- Yes.

711
00:37:52,437 --> 00:37:53,605
Because it's so unfamiliar.

712
00:37:53,688 --> 00:37:56,149
I thought this would be
a good opportunity,

713
00:37:56,232 --> 00:37:57,817
so I took the plunge.

714
00:37:58,443 --> 00:38:02,655
After today, Chef Jung Jisun will
either start believing in shamanism

715
00:38:02,739 --> 00:38:05,825
or never believe it
for the rest of her life.

716
00:38:06,826 --> 00:38:09,913
- She's not the type to take nonsense, so…
- Yes.

717
00:38:10,497 --> 00:38:12,874
The third person
for you to read is

718
00:38:12,957 --> 00:38:14,167
Jung Jisun.

719
00:38:14,250 --> 00:38:15,752
She chose the following Fate Readers.

720
00:38:18,505 --> 00:38:20,340
Manshin Kwon Sujin

721
00:38:20,423 --> 00:38:23,051
and Yoon Daeman.

722
00:38:25,220 --> 00:38:26,554
Honestly, though,

723
00:38:26,638 --> 00:38:28,890
-2 really powerful people met.
-Yes.

724
00:38:28,973 --> 00:38:32,852
They're 2 of the people
I thought would make it to the top 3.

725
00:38:32,936 --> 00:38:33,937
Same here.

726
00:38:34,020 --> 00:38:35,063
- Right?
- Yes.

727
00:38:35,146 --> 00:38:37,232
But they're going
head-to-head. Oh, no.

728
00:38:37,315 --> 00:38:38,900
One of them has to go home.

729
00:38:40,235 --> 00:38:42,737
It's a big shame
1 of us has to go.

730
00:38:42,821 --> 00:38:45,365
We were on the same team in round 3.

731
00:38:45,448 --> 00:38:46,616
Oh, good.

732
00:38:46,699 --> 00:38:48,868
We survived a battle together.

733
00:38:49,410 --> 00:38:50,703
But today,

734
00:38:50,787 --> 00:38:53,122
we're here as enemies.

735
00:38:53,623 --> 00:38:55,583
This should be fun.

736
00:38:55,667 --> 00:38:58,044
This is a survival show,
so it can't be helped.

737
00:38:58,127 --> 00:38:59,879
It'd be cooler if we went head-to-head.

738
00:38:59,963 --> 00:39:03,591
This is going to be a really close game.

739
00:39:03,675 --> 00:39:05,260
Well, as you know,

740
00:39:05,343 --> 00:39:07,220
I have many years under my belt.

741
00:39:07,303 --> 00:39:09,556
I'll go all out and make sure to win.

742
00:39:10,306 --> 00:39:13,810
I'm confident about my readings.
I think I'll win.

743
00:39:14,310 --> 00:39:16,646
I'm excited.
It's a shaman versus a shaman.

744
00:39:16,729 --> 00:39:18,147
It's a power matchup.

745
00:39:19,440 --> 00:39:22,986
Yoon Daeman
will give his reading first.

746
00:39:23,778 --> 00:39:27,031
To avoid being influenced
by Yoon Daeman's reading,

747
00:39:27,115 --> 00:39:30,743
Manshin Kwon Sujin,
please put on your headset.

748
00:39:34,497 --> 00:39:35,748
Wow…

749
00:39:36,457 --> 00:39:39,460
Yoon Daeman,
please begin your reading.

750
00:39:40,044 --> 00:39:42,213
What's your mother's surname?

751
00:39:42,297 --> 00:39:45,174
- My mother? Her surname is Choi.
- Choi.

752
00:40:05,320 --> 00:40:06,905
Look at her face.

753
00:40:06,988 --> 00:40:09,324
Her eyes got real big.

754
00:40:12,535 --> 00:40:15,455
- Chef Jung is surprised.
- She's stunned.

755
00:40:33,389 --> 00:40:36,184
Oh…
Did you always want to be a chef?

756
00:40:36,267 --> 00:40:38,561
It seems like that wasn't the case.

757
00:40:38,645 --> 00:40:40,146
Mmm…

758
00:40:40,229 --> 00:40:42,065
Did you always
want to go into cooking?

759
00:40:42,148 --> 00:40:43,900
- Initially, I wanted to be…
- Yes?

760
00:40:43,983 --> 00:40:45,193
…a day care teacher.

761
00:40:45,276 --> 00:40:47,737
Yeah, exactly.

762
00:40:47,820 --> 00:40:48,821
What?

763
00:40:49,948 --> 00:40:51,699
She wanted to be a day care teacher?

764
00:40:52,450 --> 00:40:53,660
A day care teacher?

765
00:40:53,743 --> 00:40:56,371
Really? Even I didn't know that.

766
00:40:57,330 --> 00:40:58,873
- Really?
- Even so,

767
00:40:58,957 --> 00:41:03,378
you don't seem to have any problems
with your job right now.

768
00:41:03,461 --> 00:41:05,880
But in your case, Chef Jung,

769
00:41:05,964 --> 00:41:08,216
you have a strong touch
of a General spirit.

770
00:41:08,299 --> 00:41:12,095
You need to wield a blade
in one way or another.

771
00:41:12,720 --> 00:41:14,222
It says she's been told that.

772
00:41:14,931 --> 00:41:16,683
It says she gets that a lot.

773
00:41:16,766 --> 00:41:17,892
SHE WAS TOLD SHE'S DESTINED
TO USE A KNIFE

774
00:41:17,976 --> 00:41:19,018
AND WAS A GENERAL IN A PAST LIFE

775
00:41:19,102 --> 00:41:21,896
You have to order men about,

776
00:41:21,980 --> 00:41:23,481
and you have to be the boss.

777
00:41:23,564 --> 00:41:25,108
You have to be in charge,

778
00:41:25,191 --> 00:41:28,987
and you have to keep
moving around as a leader.

779
00:41:29,070 --> 00:41:33,199
You have goegangsal, which means
you can't work under someone else.

780
00:41:33,282 --> 00:41:34,534
MEANS STRONG OPINION
AND SELF-WILL

781
00:41:34,617 --> 00:41:36,536
-That's right.
-She's nodding.

782
00:41:37,203 --> 00:41:39,330
I also see the touch of an Envoy spirit,

783
00:41:39,414 --> 00:41:41,708
so traveling abroad suits you well.

784
00:41:41,791 --> 00:41:43,292
That means

785
00:41:43,376 --> 00:41:46,629
1 of your ancestors
often traveled to China or Japan.

786
00:41:46,713 --> 00:41:47,755
That's correct.

787
00:41:48,339 --> 00:41:49,340
For real?

788
00:41:50,133 --> 00:41:52,176
Yes, she was in China.

789
00:41:52,260 --> 00:41:56,139
Actually, right now,
I'm preparing to take my business abroad.

790
00:41:56,222 --> 00:41:58,474
-My specialty is Chinese cuisine.
-Yes.

791
00:41:58,558 --> 00:42:01,936
Korean food is very popular
overseas right now,

792
00:42:02,020 --> 00:42:04,397
-and some tell me to do Korean cuisine.
-Yes.

793
00:42:04,480 --> 00:42:05,982
She's a real good Korean cuisine cook too.

794
00:42:06,065 --> 00:42:07,692
- Oh, really?
- She's good.

795
00:42:07,775 --> 00:42:12,488
I wonder if I should hop on
the K-food trend to be successful.

796
00:42:12,572 --> 00:42:14,866
From what I see,

797
00:42:14,949 --> 00:42:17,243
in your case…

798
00:42:17,326 --> 00:42:20,872
You're still a bit torn,
but you've already made up your mind.

799
00:42:20,955 --> 00:42:22,248
You want to stick to Chinese cuisine.

800
00:42:26,002 --> 00:42:27,128
- Yes.
- Am I right?

801
00:42:27,211 --> 00:42:28,254
- Yes.
- See?

802
00:42:28,337 --> 00:42:29,672
Oh…

803
00:42:30,298 --> 00:42:32,216
For real? He got that right?

804
00:42:33,259 --> 00:42:34,635
What is going on?

805
00:42:34,719 --> 00:42:35,803
Seriously?

806
00:42:38,222 --> 00:42:39,348
- Mmm…
- Mm-hmm.

807
00:42:39,432 --> 00:42:41,559
Let's see…

808
00:42:41,642 --> 00:42:43,895
I see Southeast Asia too.

809
00:42:43,978 --> 00:42:46,022
You'll become famous in Southeast Asia

810
00:42:46,105 --> 00:42:50,902
and could branch out to Europe.
That's the energy I'm feeling.

811
00:42:50,985 --> 00:42:53,362
I'm going to open a new restaurant.

812
00:42:53,446 --> 00:42:57,366
I wonder if I should do it
in Taiwan or Singapore.

813
00:42:57,450 --> 00:42:58,826
Mmm…

814
00:42:58,910 --> 00:42:59,911
Whoa.

815
00:43:00,578 --> 00:43:01,871
What the heck?

816
00:43:01,954 --> 00:43:04,624
2025, AGED 43,
PREPARING TO EXPAND BUSINESS

817
00:43:04,707 --> 00:43:07,085
IN OTHER ASIAN COUNTRIES

818
00:43:07,168 --> 00:43:09,879
I think things will go well…

819
00:43:09,962 --> 00:43:11,089
- Mmm…
- …in Taiwan for you.

820
00:43:11,172 --> 00:43:14,884
I feel you'll do better in Taiwan
than in Singapore.

821
00:43:14,967 --> 00:43:16,469
Oh…

822
00:43:16,552 --> 00:43:18,137
Also, Chef Jung.

823
00:43:19,889 --> 00:43:21,724
Don't get any plastic surgeries.

824
00:43:24,060 --> 00:43:26,437
I'm interested in
the double eyelid surgery.

825
00:43:26,521 --> 00:43:29,148
-No, don't do it.
-I've seen lots of doctors.

826
00:43:29,232 --> 00:43:30,316
Wow!

827
00:43:30,399 --> 00:43:32,193
- For real?
- Really?

828
00:43:32,693 --> 00:43:37,532
I want to look tough
so people don't look down on me.

829
00:43:37,615 --> 00:43:41,494
That's why I wear heavy eye makeup
and considered the surgery.

830
00:43:41,577 --> 00:43:43,788
She looks like a softie
without the eye makeup.

831
00:43:43,871 --> 00:43:45,039
Oh, she does?

832
00:43:45,790 --> 00:43:48,292
But in the end,
I was too scared to go through with it.

833
00:43:48,376 --> 00:43:50,002
Right, don't do it.

834
00:43:50,086 --> 00:43:53,297
You have a face that will bring you
great luck later in life.

835
00:43:53,381 --> 00:43:57,426
Your eyelids half cover your pupils.

836
00:43:57,510 --> 00:44:00,346
You're looking good as is.

837
00:44:00,888 --> 00:44:04,058
My deities say
you'll be better off without the surgery.

838
00:44:04,142 --> 00:44:06,060
No need to get surgery
when you're doing well.

839
00:44:06,144 --> 00:44:07,478
- Right.
- Wow.

840
00:44:07,562 --> 00:44:08,813
This is interesting.

841
00:44:08,896 --> 00:44:10,982
That's what I'm hearing.

842
00:44:11,065 --> 00:44:12,775
Now, about your health.

843
00:44:12,859 --> 00:44:14,902
I'm sensing

844
00:44:15,486 --> 00:44:19,031
that your uterus is a little weak.

845
00:44:21,909 --> 00:44:23,911
I see a potential woman's disease,
like in your uterus.

846
00:44:23,995 --> 00:44:26,539
So you need to be careful.

847
00:44:26,622 --> 00:44:30,209
Make sure to go see a doctor
and get checkups.

848
00:44:30,293 --> 00:44:31,752
Mmm…

849
00:44:32,879 --> 00:44:33,880
Oh, really?

850
00:44:34,505 --> 00:44:35,506
He's right.

851
00:44:36,132 --> 00:44:38,092
-He said her uterus is weak.
-Really?

852
00:44:38,176 --> 00:44:41,137
She had surgery for carcinoma
in situ of the cervix.

853
00:44:44,390 --> 00:44:47,018
I'd like to know about my son's future.

854
00:44:47,518 --> 00:44:48,686
What will he become?

855
00:44:49,228 --> 00:44:50,730
How old is he?

856
00:44:50,813 --> 00:44:54,609
- He was born in 2014.
- That's the Year of the Horse.

857
00:44:54,692 --> 00:44:55,902
Mmm…

858
00:44:55,985 --> 00:44:58,654
I'd suggest letting him get into sports.

859
00:44:59,280 --> 00:45:00,364
Woohyeong plays soccer.

860
00:45:00,907 --> 00:45:02,200
- Really?
- He plays soccer.

861
00:45:02,283 --> 00:45:03,826
- He does?
- He plays soccer.

862
00:45:03,910 --> 00:45:05,369
Ooh…

863
00:45:05,453 --> 00:45:08,956
- Ah…
- Yeah, I think he'll do well

864
00:45:09,040 --> 00:45:11,417
in sports or arts.

865
00:45:11,500 --> 00:45:12,877
But…

866
00:45:14,837 --> 00:45:18,299
There should've been 1 or 2 more kids.

867
00:45:18,382 --> 00:45:19,884
- Mmm…
- Mm-hmm…

868
00:45:20,676 --> 00:45:25,848
I'm not sure if it was before or after
your son, but you've had a miscarriage.

869
00:45:25,932 --> 00:45:28,184
I'm seeing 1 more baby.

870
00:45:33,856 --> 00:45:34,982
For real?

871
00:45:38,486 --> 00:45:41,864
- I was pregnant this year.
- Okay.

872
00:45:41,948 --> 00:45:43,407
- I lost it.
- This year?

873
00:45:43,491 --> 00:45:45,451
- You had a miscarriage this year?
- Yes.

874
00:45:45,534 --> 00:45:46,661
Mm-hmm…

875
00:45:47,328 --> 00:45:48,329
Oh, dear.

876
00:45:49,330 --> 00:45:51,290
Oh, no…

877
00:45:51,874 --> 00:45:53,125
I had no idea.

878
00:45:54,543 --> 00:45:57,630
- My son keeps saying he wants a sibling.
- I see.

879
00:45:57,713 --> 00:45:59,215
Will we have another child?

880
00:46:00,424 --> 00:46:01,634
It's likely.

881
00:46:02,134 --> 00:46:03,970
- It is? Oh…
- There is another child.

882
00:46:04,762 --> 00:46:05,930
It'll be another boy.

883
00:46:06,013 --> 00:46:07,390
But…

884
00:46:08,099 --> 00:46:09,892
There's no result without action.

885
00:46:09,976 --> 00:46:11,227
You sleep in separate rooms.

886
00:46:13,729 --> 00:46:15,356
Ah!

887
00:46:18,401 --> 00:46:19,443
What is this?

888
00:46:19,527 --> 00:46:21,028
- He's on a roll.
- He's spot-on.

889
00:46:21,112 --> 00:46:23,072
2017, AGED 35, STARTED SLEEPING
APART FROM HER HUSBAND

890
00:46:23,155 --> 00:46:24,490
He's killing it.

891
00:46:25,116 --> 00:46:27,076
How do you expect to get pregnant
with no action?

892
00:46:30,913 --> 00:46:32,456
-My gosh.
-Oh, dear.

893
00:46:33,291 --> 00:46:35,543
Go somewhere romantic.

894
00:46:36,085 --> 00:46:39,213
But when I look at you and your husband,

895
00:46:39,297 --> 00:46:41,215
I see something called gongmangsal.

896
00:46:41,299 --> 00:46:44,677
It means "empty bedroom."

897
00:46:44,760 --> 00:46:47,555
This means some distance will actually

898
00:46:48,097 --> 00:46:49,890
make things better between you and him.

899
00:46:50,558 --> 00:46:52,101
You guys don't talk much, do you?

900
00:46:53,144 --> 00:46:54,478
- No.
- Right.

901
00:46:54,562 --> 00:46:55,813
Huh? Gosh.

902
00:46:59,317 --> 00:47:00,776
- What the heck?
- What?

903
00:47:00,860 --> 00:47:02,862
Did he spy on her or something?

904
00:47:10,369 --> 00:47:14,040
I really hate emotional drain.

905
00:47:14,123 --> 00:47:18,044
Even the effort to talk
feels like hard work,

906
00:47:18,127 --> 00:47:22,214
so when I need to say something,
I'd rather send a text.

907
00:47:22,965 --> 00:47:25,051
She speaks like an AI
and talks only about work.

908
00:47:25,134 --> 00:47:28,387
- Super rational and logical.
- Totally, like a soldier.

909
00:47:28,471 --> 00:47:30,765
But that's not the case
for your husband.

910
00:47:30,848 --> 00:47:32,850
As for your husband…

911
00:47:34,143 --> 00:47:36,187
…he's a softie inside.

912
00:47:36,270 --> 00:47:38,147
- You're right.
- That's why…

913
00:47:38,230 --> 00:47:39,899
Her husband is a talker.

914
00:47:39,982 --> 00:47:41,359
He's on the sensitive side.

915
00:47:42,026 --> 00:47:43,819
He may seem like a tough guy,

916
00:47:43,903 --> 00:47:45,029
but he's really gentle.

917
00:47:45,780 --> 00:47:48,199
A tough woman
and a sensitive man are a good match.

918
00:47:49,075 --> 00:47:51,285
Your husband is a good businessman.

919
00:47:52,036 --> 00:47:53,287
He has his way with words.

920
00:47:53,996 --> 00:47:56,290
He should be in sales and business.

921
00:47:56,374 --> 00:47:57,917
Yes, that's true.

922
00:47:58,000 --> 00:48:01,253
- They run the business together.
- He's a good salesman.

923
00:48:01,337 --> 00:48:03,422
HER HUSBAND CO-OWNS THE BUSINESS

924
00:48:03,506 --> 00:48:06,258
I'm hearing that your husband has

925
00:48:06,342 --> 00:48:10,096
a lot of qualities that you don't have.

926
00:48:11,055 --> 00:48:14,642
-He and I run our business together.
-Yes.

927
00:48:14,725 --> 00:48:15,976
The thing is,

928
00:48:16,519 --> 00:48:17,728
I don't really care much

929
00:48:17,812 --> 00:48:19,397
- about ownership.
- Right.

930
00:48:19,480 --> 00:48:21,148
So when we opened the restaurant,

931
00:48:21,232 --> 00:48:23,526
I put everything in my husband's name.

932
00:48:23,609 --> 00:48:25,194
Oh, you're crazy.

933
00:48:28,948 --> 00:48:30,616
- Oh!
- Oh…

934
00:48:30,699 --> 00:48:32,451
- Did he just say, "You're crazy"?
- I know.

935
00:48:36,705 --> 00:48:40,084
- It was because I trusted him.
- Of course.

936
00:48:40,167 --> 00:48:42,336
When I first got into this industry,

937
00:48:42,420 --> 00:48:44,672
I was so belittled and looked down upon.

938
00:48:45,840 --> 00:48:47,508
What people said the most was,

939
00:48:47,591 --> 00:48:49,760
"You'll quit anyway
when you get married and have kids,

940
00:48:49,844 --> 00:48:51,720
so why work so hard?"

941
00:48:51,804 --> 00:48:53,681
That's what I heard the most.

942
00:48:53,764 --> 00:48:55,724
It's a trauma of sorts for me.

943
00:48:58,894 --> 00:49:02,064
Female Chinese cuisine chefs
were looked down upon a lot,

944
00:49:02,731 --> 00:49:03,983
so she put it in her husband's name.

945
00:49:04,066 --> 00:49:05,067
Wow…

946
00:49:05,818 --> 00:49:10,114
When it comes to who owns the business…

947
00:49:11,532 --> 00:49:14,326
I'm getting that you'll have
separate ownerships in the future.

948
00:49:14,410 --> 00:49:18,205
Starting with the next business,
it won't hurt to put it in your name.

949
00:49:20,374 --> 00:49:21,667
Oh…

950
00:49:21,750 --> 00:49:24,044
There's something
I've been wondering.

951
00:49:25,838 --> 00:49:27,715
I'm a twin.

952
00:49:27,798 --> 00:49:28,883
Oh, really?

953
00:49:30,384 --> 00:49:35,264
- We were born 40 minutes apart.
- Okay.

954
00:49:35,347 --> 00:49:37,516
My twin sister is living
a completely different life.

955
00:49:38,517 --> 00:49:41,020
- She came back from death's door.
- Mmm…

956
00:49:41,103 --> 00:49:42,480
She's still very ill.

957
00:49:42,980 --> 00:49:44,482
- Mmm…
- Oh, dear.

958
00:49:46,650 --> 00:49:48,861
Since she was a child,

959
00:49:49,445 --> 00:49:52,239
she must've had many surgeries.

960
00:49:52,323 --> 00:49:55,159
She'll have to be careful
for the next couple of years.

961
00:49:55,743 --> 00:49:57,036
This year, the next,

962
00:49:57,578 --> 00:49:58,954
and then the year after.

963
00:49:59,038 --> 00:50:01,540
- Her fortune isn't looking great.
- Ah…

964
00:50:01,624 --> 00:50:03,959
- Mmm…
- It means she may need a surgery.

965
00:50:04,043 --> 00:50:05,127
Right.

966
00:50:05,211 --> 00:50:07,421
She's physically unwell,
and it seems like

967
00:50:07,505 --> 00:50:09,173
she's mentally unwell too.

968
00:50:09,256 --> 00:50:11,467
- I sense lethargy.
- Mmm…

969
00:50:11,550 --> 00:50:14,386
It seems like she finds it
difficult to be active in life.

970
00:50:14,470 --> 00:50:16,722
-Right. She's seeing a psychiatrist,
-Yes.

971
00:50:16,805 --> 00:50:18,641
- and she's physically ill too.
- Yes, so…

972
00:50:18,724 --> 00:50:20,726
2019, AGED 37, HER TWIN SISTER
COLLAPSED FROM DIABETIC SHOCK

973
00:50:20,809 --> 00:50:22,978
This doesn't mention her mental illness.

974
00:50:23,062 --> 00:50:24,522
No, it doesn't.

975
00:50:24,605 --> 00:50:28,234
I'm getting the feeling
that she's good with her hands.

976
00:50:28,943 --> 00:50:30,319
Yes.

977
00:50:30,402 --> 00:50:33,364
She's probably good at making
cute little things.

978
00:50:33,948 --> 00:50:35,449
She's skilled with her hands.

979
00:50:35,533 --> 00:50:38,577
- Yes.
- She majored in skin care.

980
00:50:38,661 --> 00:50:40,704
She's a manicurist and a nurse's aide.

981
00:50:40,788 --> 00:50:43,082
She has over 20 qualifications,

982
00:50:43,165 --> 00:50:45,251
- but she can't put any of them to use.
- Right.

983
00:50:46,710 --> 00:50:48,546
- Wow…
- Is that so?

984
00:50:49,213 --> 00:50:50,339
You see,

985
00:50:50,422 --> 00:50:52,758
you need to help her get out there

986
00:50:52,841 --> 00:50:55,219
and pick up a hobby or something.

987
00:50:58,722 --> 00:51:00,641
The time is up.

988
00:51:04,270 --> 00:51:05,271
Okay.

989
00:51:07,147 --> 00:51:09,692
Yoon Daeman's really sharp.

990
00:51:09,775 --> 00:51:12,361
He's the one. I'm going to go see him.

991
00:51:13,237 --> 00:51:15,990
- I think this was the best one so far.
- Oh…

992
00:51:16,657 --> 00:51:18,534
I knew he'd do well.

993
00:51:20,744 --> 00:51:24,415
Manshin Kwon Sujin,
please take off the headset.

994
00:51:25,249 --> 00:51:29,378
Manshin Kwon Sujin
looks like a Gen Z in the headset.

995
00:51:30,212 --> 00:51:31,505
A Gen Z in hanbok.

996
00:51:33,048 --> 00:51:35,175
The others don't sway me.

997
00:51:35,259 --> 00:51:38,095
The deities I serve
are the most important to me.

998
00:51:38,846 --> 00:51:40,347
I'll just trust in them.

999
00:51:41,307 --> 00:51:44,059
Having lots of experience
doesn't mean my skills are stale.

1000
00:51:44,143 --> 00:51:45,477
I'm still honing them.

1001
00:51:45,978 --> 00:51:47,438
I look forward to this.

1002
00:51:48,480 --> 00:51:49,857
- Hello.
- Hello.

1003
00:51:49,940 --> 00:51:51,442
Your date of birth is…

1004
00:51:51,525 --> 00:51:54,320
It's May 23, 1983 on the lunar calendar.

1005
00:51:55,112 --> 00:51:56,280
-The Year of the Pig, right?
-Yes.

1006
00:51:58,741 --> 00:52:00,451
May 23.

1007
00:52:00,534 --> 00:52:02,244
I don't really use my tools.

1008
00:52:02,328 --> 00:52:04,955
I just write down
the client's name and date of birth.

1009
00:52:05,039 --> 00:52:08,334
I haven't waved my fan
or used my bells once.

1010
00:52:10,961 --> 00:52:12,963
You're very ambitious.

1011
00:52:15,758 --> 00:52:18,761
It says you're fated to draw
other people's envy and jealousy.

1012
00:52:19,261 --> 00:52:22,473
- Oh…
- People criticize you even if you do well.

1013
00:52:22,556 --> 00:52:25,309
You get criticized,
whether you step up or not.

1014
00:52:26,185 --> 00:52:27,394
Now,

1015
00:52:27,478 --> 00:52:31,649
are you planning on
expanding your business?

1016
00:52:32,733 --> 00:52:34,360
- Yes.
- Oh…

1017
00:52:35,110 --> 00:52:37,279
Seems like you've been
planning that for a few years.

1018
00:52:37,363 --> 00:52:39,782
You've been sowing seeds
for the last 2, 3 years.

1019
00:52:39,865 --> 00:52:40,866
Oh…

1020
00:52:40,949 --> 00:52:42,368
That's true.

1021
00:52:42,451 --> 00:52:44,495
2022, AGED 40,
OPENED SECOND RESTAURANT

1022
00:52:44,578 --> 00:52:47,247
AFTER THE FIRST BRANCH REACHED
MONTHLY SALES OF 100 MILLION WON

1023
00:52:47,331 --> 00:52:49,249
Are you against franchising?

1024
00:52:50,292 --> 00:52:51,960
- Yes.
- Right?

1025
00:52:52,044 --> 00:52:53,379
You want to be hands-on.

1026
00:52:53,462 --> 00:52:55,714
You don't want to expand
by bringing in others.

1027
00:52:55,798 --> 00:52:59,468
You want to do only what you can handle
and do it perfectly,

1028
00:52:59,551 --> 00:53:01,387
whether it's 3 restaurants or 5.

1029
00:53:01,470 --> 00:53:04,515
-That's how you feel.
-That's right.

1030
00:53:04,598 --> 00:53:05,599
What, really?

1031
00:53:05,683 --> 00:53:07,851
She only has 2 locations,
in Hongdae and Seocho.

1032
00:53:07,935 --> 00:53:09,103
Oh…

1033
00:53:10,187 --> 00:53:12,314
- She doesn't want to franchise.
